My thesis was just:
I like the cat‚Ä¶
*collector/investor perspective
I‚Äôm echoing @fungibleartist‚Äôs take but from a collectible perspective. Laur is herself another artist I‚Äôve supported with @uwucrewnft aka my NFT family https://t.co/GmUFZWFHOi

Added bonus that artists with strong existing reputations *IN WEB3* are unlikely to rug, are likely to understand the culture/how to create value, very unlikely to fall off 

I‚Äôm also not trying to dehumanize artists is pursuit of profit, just being real about investment thesisü§ç

It also creates a liquid market w/ higher consensus vs. 1/1s for exposure to these artist‚Äôs work. Picking winners in NFTs post mint is about picking brands, and artists are a brand. Existing successful artists imo have strong asymmetric chances of success over other collections

Artists are the most natural, sustainable, logical source of new reasons for exposure for a collection they‚Äôve launched, alongside the community of owners and any utility. If done well, the success of their 1/1s feeds value into their collectible and vice versa

The biggest issue in NFTs is how do you survive market dumps, and by ‚Äúsurvive‚Äù I mean reclaim attention in an attention economy that has a strong recency bias and affinity to gamble mints

In order to survive, you either need utility, strong community or reasons for new exposure
